(https://www.scmr.com/glossary)\n- [Companies](https://www.scmr.com/company/all)\n- [Visionaries](https://www.scmr.com/resources/category/visionaries)\n- [White Papers](https://www.scmr.com/resources/category/papers)\n- [Special Reports](https://www.scmr.com/resources/category/special-reports)\n- [Premiums](https://www.scmr.com/resources/category/premiums)\n- [Magazine Archive](https://www.scmr.com/archive/all)\n\n- ##### [Subscribe](https://peerless.omeda.com/scmr/r-paid.do?p=WEBPDSCMR)\n\n- [SCMR Magazine](https://peerless.omeda.com/scmr/r-paid.do?p=WEBPDSCMR)\n- [Newsletters](https://www.scmr.com/site/subscribe)\n- [Magazine Archives](https://www.scmr.com/archive/all)\n- [Customer Service](https://www.scmr.com/site/contact_us)\n\n- ##### [Latest](https://www.scmr.com/topic/)\n\n\n- [Podcast: Talking Supply Chain: How logistics leaders are winning in volatile times](https://www.scmr.com/podcast/talking-supply-chain-how-logistics-leaders-are-winning-in-volatile-times)\n- [Webinar: Amazon Supply Chain 101: Enabling efficiency and growth for businesses everywhere\u2014and everywhere they sell](https://www.scmr.com/article/amazon-supply-chain-101-enabling-efficiency-and-growth-for-businesses-everywhereand-everywhere-they-sell)\n- [News: NextGen extends 2026 award, speaker submission deadlines amid strong industry interest](https://www.scmr.com/article/nextgen-extends-2026-award-speaker-submission-deadlines-amid-strong-industry-interest)\n- [News: What It Really Means: Being in the business of supply](https://www.scmr.com/article/what-it-really-means-being-in-the-business-of-supply)\n- [Artificial Intelligence: NextGen extends 2026 award, speaker submission deadlines amid strong industry interest](https://www.scmr.com/article/nextgen-extends-2026-award-speaker-submission-deadlines-amid-strong-industry-interest)\n- [NextGen Supply Chain Conference: NextGen extends 2026 award, speaker submission deadlines amid strong industry interest](https://www.scmr.com/article/nextgen-extends-2026-award-speaker-submission-deadlines-amid-strong-industry-interest)\n- [Research: Supply chain salaries, job satisfaction on the rise](https://www.scmr.com/article/supply-chain-salaries-job-satisfaction-on-the-rise)\n- [More news](https://www.scmr.com/news/all/)\n\n# How P&G\u2019s One Supply Chain strategy exemplifies the Perfect Order\n\n#### Abiding by the foundational principles of the Perfect Order shows how supply chain execution can drive customer value, availability, and long-term business growth\n\nSubscriber: [Log Out](https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order#)\n\n[Norman Katz](https://www.scmr.com/author/nkatz) \u00b7\n\nMarch 16, 2026 \u00b7 [Post to Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order/&t=How%20P&G%E2%80%99s%20One%20Supply%20Chain%20strategy%20exemplifies%20the%20Perfect%20Order \"Post to Facebook\")[Tweet](https://twitter.com/intent/tweet?source=https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order/&text=How%20P&G%E2%80%99s%20One%20Supply%20Chain%20strategy%20exemplifies%20the%20Perfect%20Order \"Tweet\")[Post to Linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/shareArticle?mini=true&url=https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order/&title=How%20P&G%E2%80%99s%20One%20Supply%20Chain%20strategy%20exemplifies%20the%20Perfect%20Order&source=Supply%20Chain%20Management%20Review \"Post to Linkedin\")[Send by Email](mailto:?email=&subject=How%20P&G%E2%80%99s%20One%20Supply%20Chain%20strategy%20exemplifies%20the%20Perfect%20Order&body=How%20P&G%E2%80%99s%20One%20Supply%20Chain%20strategy%20exemplifies%20the%20Perfect%20Order,%20https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order/ \"Send by Email\")\n\n## Executive Takeaways\n\n- **The Perfect Order framework still defines supply chain excellence.** Dr. Edward J. Marien\u2019s eight \u201ccustomer rights\u201d\u2014from the right product and quantity to the right cost and documentation\u2014remain a foundational blueprint for modern supply chain performance.\n- **P&G operationalized the Perfect Order through its One Supply Chain strategy.** By aligning forecasting, logistics, supplier partnerships, and product supply operations, Procter & Gamble built an integrated network designed to ensure product availability wherever and whenever consumers shop.\n- **Supply chain execution is a competitive differentiator.** P&G\u2019s evolution since the 1990s shows how operational excellence, rather than cost-cutting alone, can create brand leadership in competitive consumer goods markets.\n- **Perfect Order principles apply to companies of any size.** Organizations do not need the scale of P&G to adopt the eight customer rights; focusing on reliability, availability, and value creation can strengthen customer relationships and revenue growth.\n\nIn February 2025, Supply Chain Management Review (SCMR) published my 12-part online article series on the [Perfect Order](https://www.scmr.com/article/norman-katz-article-series-outlines-the-steps-to-achieving-the-perfect-order). The article series\u2014with accompanying \u201cexplainer\u201d articles\u2014was based on a single article written 20 years prior by Dr. Edward J. Marien that presented a (business) customer\u2019s eight rights when ordering goods.\n\nTo recap Dr. Marien\u2019s eight customer rights (8Rs) for logistics professionals, a customer deserves:\n\n1. The Right Product\n2. In the Right Quantity\n3. From the Right Source\n4. To the Right Destination\n5. In the Right Condition\n6. At the Right Time\n7. With the Right Documentation\n8. At the Right Cost\n\nIn the May/June 2025 edition of Supply Chain Management Review magazine, SCMR Editor In Chief Brian Straight (who edited my article series) authored a thought-provoking article titled \u201c [How supply chain leadership drives business growth, competitive advantage](https://www.scmr.com/article/how-procter-and-gamble-supply-chain-leadership-drives-business-growth).\u201d Brian\u2019s article focused on how P&G\u2019s unified supply chain strategies have helped them to grow the company and become brand leaders.\n\nWhat I found so interesting about Brian\u2019s article is how much of P&G\u2019s supply chain strategy paralleled Dr. Marien\u2019s foundational customer rights. Let me draw out the comments and quotes from Brian\u2019s article and the relationship to Dr. Marien\u2019s 8Rs.\n\n1. The Right Product, The Right Time, and The Right Destination: \u201cAs the strategy has evolved, it has remained consistent in its approach to satisfy the customer\u2019s desire and need for the right product when and where it was needed.\u201d\n2. The Right Time and The Right Destination: \u201cIt is the importance of being on the shelf, online, wherever and whenever people want to shop.\u201d (P&G\u2019s chief product supply officer.)\n3. The Right Quantity: \u201cFor beauty and personal care brands, that has meant winning consumers through superior innovation delivered at speed, and ensuring product availability.\u201d\n4. From the Right Source: \u201cSupply chain leaders at P&G align operations with corporate strategy to meet evolving consumer demands, leveraging advanced logistics, strategic supplier partnerships, and real-time demand forecasting.\u201d\n5. In the Right Condition: \u201cIt also means producing quality products so that customers have a superior experience when they use our brands.\u201d (P&G\u2019s chief product supply officer)\n\nAccording to Brian\u2019s article, P&G didn\u2019t just launch head-on into their unified One Supply Chain strategy; it was an evolutionary process that began in the 1990s and matured through three distinct iterations. As P&G has proven: execution\u2014from one end of its supply chain to the other\u2014became its competitive edge in a commoditized world. If these words sound familiar, it\u2019s because you\u2019ve read them from me before.\n\n#### Related content\n\n[The Perfect Order needs to include the right data](https://www.scmr.com/article/the-perfect-order-needs-to-include-the-right-data)\n\n[Are you data-ready or in data-despair?](https://www.scmr.com/article/are-you-data-ready-or-in-data-despair)\n\n[AI will not solve the problems of Big Data](https://www.scmr.com/article/ai-will-not-solve-the-problems-of-big-data)\n\n[Closing the gaps in business tax collection](https://www.scmr.com/article/closing-the-gaps-in-business-tax-collection)\n\nYour company does not need to be as big as P&G to ensure that it is providing each and every customer their rights when they order a product from you, regardless of whether that customer is a business or that customer is a person.\u00a0 As Brian\u2019s article concludes, you need to view your supply chain as a driver of revenue.\u00a0 Stop thinking about cutting costs and start thinking about value propositions.\u00a0Because even if you are not, your competitors probably are.\n\nMy Perfect Order article series can be viewed at:\u00a0[https://www.scmr.com/article/norman-katz-article-series-outlines-the-steps-to-achieving-the-perfect-order](https://www.scmr.com/article/norman-katz-article-series-outlines-the-steps-to-achieving-the-perfect-order)\n\n## FAQs\n\n#### Q: What is the Perfect Order in supply chain management?\n\nThe Perfect Order is a logistics framework based on delivering the right product, in the right quantity, from the right source, to the right destination, in the right condition, at the right time, with the right documentation, and at the right cost.\n\n#### Q: What is Procter & Gamble\u2019s One Supply Chain strategy?\n\nP&G\u2019s One Supply Chain strategy integrates planning, logistics, supplier partnerships, and manufacturing operations into a unified system designed to ensure product availability and meet consumer demand efficiently.\n\n#### Q: How does P&G demonstrate the Perfect Order concept?\n\nThrough real-time demand forecasting, coordinated supplier networks, strong product quality controls, and a focus on product availability across physical and digital channels, P&G aligns its operations with the eight customer rights.\n\n#### Q: Why is the Perfect Order important for modern supply chains?\n\nThe framework shifts the focus from simply reducing costs to delivering consistent customer value and reliable execution, which can drive competitive advantage and long-term business growth.\n\n## SC  MR\n\n![Abiding by the foundational principles of the Perfect Order shows how supply chain execution can drive customer value, availability, and long-term business growth.](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/perfect-order-GettyImages-1157145061.jpg)\n\n(Photo: Getty Images)\n\nAbiding by the foundational principles of the Perfect Order shows how supply chain execution can drive customer value, availability, and long-term business growth.\n\n![](https://www.scmr.com/images/prototype/email-newsletter-image.jpg)\n\nSubscribe to our weekly e-mail update\n\nDon\u2019t miss out on the best in supply chain. Get premium\nresources and in-depth, comprehensive feature articles written by the industry's top experts \u2013 delivered.\n\nSubscribe!\n\n\\*Please enter a valid email address.\n\n##### More Perfect Order\n\n- [How P&G\u2019s One Supply Chain strategy exemplifies the Perfect Order](https://www.scmr.com/article/how-pgs-one-supply-chain-strategy-exemplifies-the-perfect-order)\n- [The Perfect Order: Introduction](https://www.scmr.com/article/the-perfect-order-introduction)\n- [Explainer: What is EDI?](https://www.scmr.com/article/explainer-what-is-edi)\n- [Explainer: The basics of barcodes](https://www.scmr.com/article/explainer-the-basics-of-barcodes)\n- [The Perfect Order: Defining the customer](https://www.scmr.com/article/the-perfect-order-defining-the-customer)\n- [More Perfect Order](https://www.scmr.com/topic/tag/Perfect_Order)\n\n[Explore Procurement & Sourcing](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/procurement)\n\n### ![](https://www.scmr.com/images/prototype/telescope.jpg) Explore\n\n##### Topics\n\n- [News](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/news)\n- [Visionaries](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/visionaries)\n- [Procurement & Sourcing](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/procurement)\n- [Inventory Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/inventory-management)\n- [Business Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/management)\n- [Supply Chain Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/supply-chain-management)\n- [Norman Katz](https://www.scmr.com/topic/tag/Norman_Katz)\n- [One Supply Chain](https://www.scmr.com/topic/tag/One_Supply_Chain)\n- [P&G](https://www.scmr.com/topic/tag/P&G)\n- [Perfect Order](https://www.scmr.com/topic/tag/Perfect_Order)\n\n##### Procurement & Sourcing News\n\n- [It isn\u2019t just about gas prices](https://www.scmr.com/article/strait-of-hormuz-iran-gas-prices)\n- [Penske Logistics jumps into the end-to-end visibility pool as industry options grow](https://www.scmr.com/article/penske-logistics-jumps-into-the-end-to-end-visibility-pool-as-industry-options-grow)\n- [Why do supply chains need to think beyond sustainability?](https://www.scmr.com/article/why-do-supply-chains-need-to-think-beyond-sustainability)\n- [Agentic AI is turning long-tail purchase orders into true cost savings](https://www.scmr.com/article/agentic-ai-is-turning-long-tail-purchase-orders-into-true-cost-savings)\n- [Amazon opens its supply chain network to everyone](https://www.scmr.com/article/amazon-opens-its-supply-chain-network-to-everyone)\n- [From scan events to continuous visibility: Every warehouse move becomes data](https://www.scmr.com/article/from-scan-events-to-continuous-visibility)\n- [More Procurement & Sourcing](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/procurement)\n\n##### Latest Procurement & Sourcing Resources\n\n[![](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/TSC_Bob_Daymon_Uber_Freight_web.jpg)\\\\\n\\\\\nTalking Supply Chain: How logistics leaders are winning in volatile times](https://www.scmr.com/podcast/talking-supply-chain-how-logistics-leaders-are-winning-in-volatile-times)\n\nIn a supply chain environment defined by tariff uncertainty, tight capacity, and constant disruption, logistics leaders are winning by\u2026\n\n[Listen in](https://www.scmr.com/podcast/talking-supply-chain-how-logistics-leaders-are-winning-in-volatile-times)\n\n- [Talking Supply Chain: AI and the new trade barrier](https://www.scmr.com/podcast/talking-supply-chain-ai-and-the-new-trade-barrier)\n- [Talking Supply Chain: Rethinking supplier relationships](https://www.scmr.com/podcast/talking-supply-chain-rethinking-supplier-relationships)\n- [More resources](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/resources)\n\n### About the Author\n\n##### [Norman Katz, President of Katzscan](https://www.scmr.com/author/nkatz)\n\n![Norman Katz's Bio Photo](https://www.scmr.com/images/avatars/avatar_103.jpg)\n\nNorman Katz is president of [Katzscan Inc.](https://katzscan.com/) a supply chain technology and operations consultancy that specializes in vendor compliance, ERP, EDI, and barcode applications.\u00a0 Norman is the author of \u201c [Detecting and Reducing Supply Chain Fraud](http://www.supplychainfraud.com/)\u201d (Gower/Routledge, 2012), \u201c [Successful Supply Chain Vendor Compliance](http://www.vendorcompliance.info/)\u201d (Gower/Routledge, 2016), and \u201c [Attack, Parry, Riposte: A Fencer\u2019s Guide To Better Business Execution](http://www.attackparryriposte.com/)\u201d (Austin Macauley, 2020). Norman is a U.S. national and international speaker and article writer, and a foil and saber fencer and fencing instructor.\n\n[View Norman's author profile.](https://www.scmr.com/author/nkatz)\n\nFollow SCMR on social media.\n\n[@SupplyChainManagementReview on Facebook](https://www.facebook.com/SupplyChainManagementReview)\n\n[@SCMR on Twitter](https://twitter.com/SCMR/)\n\n[SCMR on Linkedin](https://www.linkedin.com/showcase/scmr)\n\n### Subscribe\n\n![](https://www.scmr.com/images/prototype/scmr_cover.jpg)\n\n###### Supply Chain Management Review delivers the best industry content.\n\nSubscribe today and get full access to all of Supply Chain Management Review\u2019s exclusive content, email newsletters, premium resources and in-depth, comprehensive feature articles written by the industry's top experts on the subjects that matter most to supply chain professionals.\n\n[Subscribe today](https://peerless.omeda.com/scmr/r-main.do?p=WEBPDSCMR)\n\n![](https://scg-scmr.s3.amazonaws.com/images/site/tablets.jpg)\n\n### Editors\u2019 Picks\n\n[![](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/_resize/ai-hand-GettyImages-1221776897_resize_8a6c323291c914b43f9f252f137b3568.jpg)\\\\\n\\\\\nAI in the supply chain: From pilot programs to P&L impact](https://www.scmr.com/article/ai-in-the-supply-chain-from-pilot-programs-to-pl-impact)\n\nAI in supply chains is shifting from pilot programs to measurable P&L\u2026\n\n[![](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/_resize/Awards-NextGen-Promo_resize_8a6c323291c914b43f9f252f137b3568.jpg)\\\\\n\\\\\nNextGen revamps awards for 2026, opens submissions](https://www.scmr.com/article/nextgen-revamps-awards-for-2026-opens-submissions)\n\nThe NextGen Supply Chain Conference has revamped its 2026 awards to emphasize\u2026\n\n[![](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/_resize/ai-pedestal-GettyImages-2195337175_resize_8a6c323291c914b43f9f252f137b3568.jpg)\\\\\n\\\\\n\u2018AI is eating software\u2019 and it is redefining supply chain decision-making as a result](https://www.scmr.com/article/ai-eating-software-redefining-supply-chain-decision-making)\n\nAgentic AI is transforming supply chains from deterministic, rule-based\u2026\n\n[![](https://www.scmr.com/images/2026_article/_resize/lens-GettyImages-2164609178_resize_8a6c323291c914b43f9f252f137b3568.jpg)\\\\\n\\\\\nWhat\u2019s the missing ingredient in supply chain visibility?](https://www.scmr.com/article/whats-the-missing-ingredient-in-supply-chain-visibility)\n\nTrue supply chain visibility in 2026 depends less on tracking shipments and\u2026\n\n\u00a9 Copyright 2026 Supply Chain Management Review, a division of Peerless Media. All Rights Reserved.\n\n\u00d7\n\n## [Search](https://www.scmr.com/search)\n\n[Search](https://www.scmr.com/search)\n\n## [Sourcing & Procurement](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/procurement)\n\n[Inventory Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/inventory-management) [Risk Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/risk-management) [Global Trade](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/global-trade) [Ports & Shipping](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/ports-shipping)\n\n## [Business Management](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/management)\n\n[Supply Chain](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/supply-chain-management) [TMS](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/tms) [WMS](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/wms) [3PL](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/3pl) [Government & Regulation](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/govt-regulation) [Sustainability](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/sustainability) [Finance](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/finance)\n\n## [Software & Technology](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/software-technology)\n\n[Artificial Intelligence](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/artificial-intelligence) [Automation](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/automation) [Cloud](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/cloud) [IoT](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/iot) [Robotics](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/robotics) [Software](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/software)\n\n## [The Academy](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/the-academy)\n\n[Executive Education](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/executive-education) [Associations](https://www.scmr.com/topic/category/associations) 