Payload:
{
  "source_system": "web",
  "source_object_type": "web_page",
  "source_object_id": "https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html",
  "content": "Oops, something went wrong\n\n[Skip to navigation](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html#navigation-container) [Skip to main content](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html#nimbus-app) [Skip to right column](https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html#right-rail)\n\n[![Supply Chain Dive](https://s.yimg.com/ny/api/res/1.2/K2TuQpFY2P5Pn9HtcCR29g--/YXBwaWQ9aGlnaGxhbmRlcjt3PTM1MjtoPTQ4/https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2024-10/cddd9d60-9304-11ef-99d7-9fb464d37576)](https://www.supplychaindive.com/ \"Supply Chain Dive\")\n\n# P&G shifts Supply Chain 3.0, other platforms into large-scale rollout\n\nAntone Gonsalves\n\nMay 8, 20262 min read\n\n- [PG \\\\\n  -0.80%](https://finance.yahoo.com/quote/PG/ \"PG\")\n\n\n_This story was originally published on [Supply Chain Dive](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/pg-shifts-supply-chain-30-other-platforms-into-large-scale-rollout/819256/?utm_campaign=Yahoo-Licensed-Content&utm_source=yahoo&utm_medium=referral). To receive daily news and insights, subscribe to our free daily [Supply Chain Dive newsletter](https://www.supplychaindive.com/signup/?utm_campaign=Yahoo-Licensed-Content&utm_source=yahoo&utm_medium=referral)._\n\nProcter & Gamble has brought its Supply Chain 3.0 initiative into full rollout across the company as part of the underlying platforms and capabilities it has spent years building, CFO Andre Schulten said [on an April 24 earnings call](https://seekingalpha.com/article/4893993-the-procter-and-gamble-company-pg-q3-2026-earnings-call-transcript).\n\nThe supply chain initiative,\u00a0[launched in 2023](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/procter-gamble-supply-chain-restructuring/750640/), is driving a more complete systems integration from customer order to production planning and material ordering, Schulten told investors. The project applies technology, with only some AI and the rest more basic automation in P&G's manufacturing and supply chain processes.\n\nThis effort is part of a broader plan to tie research and development, supply chain, and procurement together to enable P&G to adjust sourcing, fine-tune its product formulations, and qualify alternative supplies faster and more effectively, Schulten said.\n\n\u201cIt took years to build these underlying platforms and capabilities, and we are now in full scaling mode across the company,\" he said.\n\nP&G\u2019s goal is to save up to $1.5 billion in cost of goods sold as a result of Supply Chain 3.0, Schulten [told investors last October](https://seekingalpha.com/article/4833122-the-procter-and-gamble-company-pg-q1-2026-earnings-call-transcript). Previously, executives said the project would also deliver [98% on-shelf and online availability](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/procter-gamble-supply-chain-restructuring/750640/).\n\nThe consumer goods manufacturer expects the savings to come from automation that loads and unloads finished products, packaging and raw materials even when the warehouses are unstaffed, Schulten said in the latest earnings call.\n\nAt the Barclays Annual Global Consumer Staples Conference last September, Schulten said [Supply Chain 3.0 includes](https://seekingalpha.com/article/4819464-the-procter-and-gamble-company-pg-presents-at-barclays-18th-annual-global-consumer-staples) installing warehouse technology that increases density by 50% and delivers two to three times more throughput.\n\nIn addition, the company has been piloting a four-hour night shift in Berlin run entirely through automation and robotics, one of nine pilots, executives said. Each automated shift can deliver between 15% and 60% productivity improvement, according to Schulten.\n\nP&G has set a 2030 implementation target for Supply Chain 3.0 and is moving as quickly as possible toward that mark, Schulten said on the April earnings call.\n\n\"We know it works, and we know what to do,\" Schulten said. \"We have the technologies available. It's about how fast do we roll them out. And I think that's where we'll push the envelope.\"\n\nOther CPG manufacturers are deploying supply chain technology to improve operations while cutting costs. [PepsiCo is testing](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/pepsico-uses-digital-twins-to-trial-plant-changes-nvidia-siemens/809558/) AI and digital twin technologies in plant and warehouse facilities,\u00a0[Hormel Foods is modernizing](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/hormel-supply-chain-ai-planning-platform/816293/) its supply chain with an AI planning platform, and [Hershey is projecting](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/hershey-100m-inventory-cut-supply-chain-tech/816785/) a $100 million inventory cut from technology deployed across its supply chain.\n\nStory Continues\n\n**Recommended Reading**\n\n- [P&G aims for resiliency with supply chain redesign](https://www.supplychaindive.com/news/procter-gamble-supply-chain-restructuring/750640/?utm_campaign=Yahoo-Licensed-Content-rreditorial&utm_source=yahoo&utm_medium=newsfeed)\n\n\nView Comments\n\n[Terms](https://guce.yahoo.com/terms?locale=en-US) and [Privacy Policy](https://guce.yahoo.com/privacy-policy?locale=en-US)\n\n[Your Privacy Choices ![](https://s.yimg.com/dv/static/siteApp/img/privacy-choice-control.png)](https://guce.yahoo.com/state-controls?locale=en-US&state=VA)\n\n[More Info](https://finance.yahoo.com/more-info)",
  "principal": {
    "external_id": "t1",
    "display_name": "t1"
  },
  "title": "P&G shifts Supply Chain 3.0, other platforms into large-scale rollout",
  "metadata": {
    "fetched_url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html",
    "fetched_by": "testing_bot",
    "title": "P&G shifts Supply Chain 3.0, other platforms into large-scale rollout",
    "description": "The CPG maker expects to bolster productivity through automation deployed globally in warehouses and manufacturing plants."
  },
  "source_url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/sectors/technology/articles/p-g-shifts-supply-chain-071600561.html"
}
