Headers: {'host': 'localhost:8080', 'accept-encoding': 'gzip, deflate', 'connection': 'keep-alive', 'user-agent': 'python-httpx/0.28.1', 'authorization': 'Bearer mk_live_f7a755201bdb40008c81c352343aab27_hRLnnmN3b9WoX-HWDtT0RO33t5ZOwYs1F8nQWxD1FpU', 'content-type': 'application/json', 'accept': 'application/json', 'content-length': '12190'}
Payload:
{
  "source_system": "web",
  "source_object_type": "web_page",
  "source_object_id": "https://www.pgcareers.com/global/en/supply-chain-logistics",
  "content": "-\n\n-\n\n![pAGES](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/area-supply_chain_logistics-1738938556057.jpg)\n\nMove world-renowned brands,\n\nfrom Day 1.\n\n[View all Supply Chain and Logistics opportunities](https://www.pgcareers.com/global/en/supply-chain-logistics#search-results \"View all Supply Chain and Logistics opportunities\")\n\nP&G Supply Chain & Logistics is a global business area. Here, we continually innovate best practices and technology, plan the demand and supply for markets, work with big data, design innovative algorithms, and create the physical design of our end-to-end supply networks across the world.\n\nWe consider our operations as the engine that accelerates value creation. Our teams work to ensure our products reach stores in the right quantities, at the right time, and with perfect quality. Whether you are working on a new product launch or driving efficiency in a complex supply chain, you will face a new challenge every day that you will always rise to, from Day 1.\n\n## **Supply Chain & Logistics\u00a0Roles**\n\nWe undertake a range of projects and activities to ensure P&G products reach our customers when and where they are needed. It\u2019s a world of transportation, customer service, planning, and warehousing where every team and employee plays an important role in our success.\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0556-1724785714673.jpg)\n\n- Act as a leader, while increasing productivity, capacity, and value creation through data utilization\n\n- Explore improvement opportunities to eliminate losses and simplify processes\n\n- Collaborate with internal/external customers to resolve issues and drive supply network improvements\n\n- Focus on acquiring data analysis to enable Joint Value Creation (JVC) and NOS growth with customers\n\n- Lead data issue resolution and communication\n\n- Assist planner or leader with critical tasks such as time and quality management\n\n- Own the project schedule creation and tracking and status reporting\n\n- Perform key testing scenarios and tracks overall testing phase result\n\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0529-1724785841912.jpg)\n\n- Lead the development of regional material operating strategies\n- Input into the definition and development of global standards and their \u201cfitness for use\u201d for adoption\n- Lead and support Key User Network\n- Develop and provide training\n- Provide high-level implementation support to include coaching Business Unit resources\n- Provide high-level work process support\n- Own the development of technology and business process improvements\n- Ensure work system is executed correctly for adoption and governance\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0402-1724785989728.jpg)\n\n- Acts as first level of support/coaching for work system for end users\n- Leads and deploys technical and process changes, system upgrades, and improvements\n- Participate in occasional development and user acceptance testing on new technology and processes\n- Share best practices with end users\n- Communicate, coordinate, and validate issues and improvements\n- Own security processes for technology to maintain proper registration\n- Support the qualification process as needed for keystroke and work process integration\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0686-1724785421246.jpg)\n\n- Provide clear direction relative to maintaining control of the system\n- Own and ensure the capability of the right resources, technology, skills, and financial support exists and is known\n- Lead change management decisions and interventions\n- Ensure system is evaluated for losses through value stream analysis\n- Ensure status of system versus operating strategy is known and communicated, and action plans are in place for any gaps\n- Actively partner with other functions and process owners\n- Develop action plan to deliver business targets\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0935-1724785424231.jpg)\n\n- Develop and confirm plans meet business requirements for the next 18 months\n- Apply operating strategy to parameter management\n- Maintain data used, and gather, document, and align key assumptions\n- Communicate requirements for process/technology improvements\n- Manage day-to-day activities of process, including leading resolution of conflicts and adjustment of plans\n- Develop action plan with results targets\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI9950-1724785426951.jpg)\n\n- Lead business result improvement efforts via work process improvement including the analysis, definition, design, implementation, and sustainment of improvement\n- Drive continuous improvement of an existing process via WPI and FI processes\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI1152-1724785429145.jpg)\n\n- Own the governance, mastery, and innovation\n- Own the definition of global standards and ensure their \u201cfitness for use\" for adoption\n- Own benchmarking of best practices externally and internally and adjusts standards as needed\n- Ensure technology and work processes deliver desired business results\n- Own calibration for the standards of excellence\n- Manage business experts as required for direction and prioritization\n- Responsible for critical interventions on key business issues\n- Responsible for working and addressing critical integration points\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0545-1724785624493.jpg)\n\n- Handle daily repetitive/transactional work \"within\" the processes\n- Understand work processes and utilizes best practices\n- Carry out basic system execution and data maintenance\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/UNNI0518-1724785915453.jpg)\n\n- Ensure project objectives and success criteria have been established and are aligned by sponsors\n- Ensure robust plans are created to deliver the project success criteria\n- Ensure a communication plan exists and is active\n- Organize and lead the project team for successful delivery of the project\n- Ensure key systems are in place and functioning effectively\n\n## Career Growth\n\nAt P&G Supply Chain & Logistics, you\u2019ll receive exciting hands-on tasks from Day 1. Through a wide range of challenging projects, you'll continually gain useful knowledge and experience. You'll also get constant mentorship and performance monitoring to identify when you\u2019re ready to move on to the next stage of your P&G career.\n\nAdditionally, you\u2019ll be supported by our strategic leadership development programs, so you can start your path toward becoming a successful P&G leader and supply chain master.\n\n## Supply Chain & Logistics Diciplines\n\nFocused on governing the most innovative business planning processes in the industry.\n\nDelivers new initiatives and product innovations through our supply chains.\n\nEnables P&G to be the #1 supply chain partner for our customers.\u00a0 It acts as a disproportionate source of joint value creation for the company through direct collaboration with our business partners.\n\nInvolved with the transportation, warehousing and customization of P&G products, driving efficiency and savings in one of the most dynamic parts of the supply chain.\n\nFocused on short and long-term supply replenishment planning, leveraging end-to-end loss elimination and break-through supply chain analytics to enable synchronized supply chains that maximize return.\n\n![img1](https://cdn.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/PGBPGNGLOBAL/images/cropChild-EVakP-1719504322049.png)\n\n**Even if you didn't find the perfect match today, don't miss out on future opportunities! Sign up for our talent community to get a glimpse of our company culture, stay updated on exciting events and relevant openings, and explore diverse career paths**\n\n[Sign Up Now](https://www.pgcareers.com/global/en/jointalentcommunity \"Sign Up Now\")\n\n## **FAQ**\n\n1\\. What is Supply Network Operations and how does it relate to Supply Chain Management and Logistics?\n\nSupply network operations (SNO) is a term used internally at P&G instead of the term supply chain & logistics. It is an umbrella term that covers transportation, customer service, planning, warehousing, and other aspects of our business area.\n\n2\\. What jobs are there within P&G Supply Chain & Logistics?\n\nIt takes a diverse range of roles to operate a successful, global supply chain. Jobs vary from market to market but include supply chain managers, analysts, planning specialists, logistics managers, and more, including roles unique to specific locations, such as supply networks specialists, which you\u2019ll find in the US.\n\n3\\. What does a P&G Supply Chain Manager do?\n\nSupply chain managers at P&G are responsible for forecasting customer demand, executing production plans, ensuring information is shared and accessible throughout the entire supply chain, managing the physical flow of products, and so much more.\n\n4\\. What skills do I need to work in Supply Chain Management?\n\nStudents and entry level applicants will be taught everything they need to know to succeed and have access to leadership development opportunities. What we look for are people who demonstrate the ability or potential to collaborate, communicate effectively, influence, negotiate, analyze, and strategize. Experienced professionals applying for senior positions will have demonstrated strong leadership within a business, supply chain, engineering or similar degree, and at least three years sourcing and/or supply experience.\n\n### No results for   \"${pageStateData.searchKeyword}\"\n\n### No results for   \"${pageStateData.placeVal}\"\n\nWould you like to consider the job categories below?\n\n\nClose Filter\n\n\n## Refine your search\n\nCategory\n\n\nSearch in Category\n\n\nCategory\n\n- Supply Chain and Logistics(0)\n\nCountry/Region\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nSearch in Country/Region\n\n\nCountry/Region\n\nState / Province\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nSearch in State / Province\n\n\nState / Province\n\nCity\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nSearch in City\n\n\nCity\n\nSchedule\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nSchedule\n\nSub Category\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nSub Category\n\nExperience Level\n\n\nExperience Level\n\n- Internships (0)\n- Recent Grads/Entry Level - Campus (0)\n- Recent Grads/Entry Level (0)\n- Experienced Professionals (0)\n\nLocation\n\n\nNo data found.\n\n\nLocation\n\nSearch in location\n\nSearch in Location\n\n\nClear text\n\n\nLocation\n\n\nLocation range slider\n\n\nDistance:50miles Distance:50+miles\n\nRefine Search\n\n## Showing 0 results for\"\"\n\n- Resume based\n\nClose\n\nResume based\n\n- Internships\n- Recent Grads/Entry Level - Campus\n- Recent Grads/Entry Level\n- Experienced Professionals\n- Supply Chain and Logistics\n- Clear all\n\nthe results are updated\n\n\nSearch from\nbelow listclear textGo\n\nSort by:\n\nMost relevantMost recent\n\nFilter\n\n![No jobs found](https://assets.phenompeople.com/CareerConnectResources/prod/PGBPGNGLOBAL/en_global/desktop/assets/images/no_jobs_found.png)\n\n### There are no jobs for your search criteria.\n\nPlease search again.\n\n- Back\n- Next\n\nf73e8c16622f4de49678f5882bf97aa8",
