tion\n\n\n[Colin Ricardo](https://au.linkedin.com/in/colin-ricardo?trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment_actor-name)\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n9mo\n\n\n\n- [Report this comment](https://www.linkedin.com/uas/login?session_redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fpulse%2Fhow-procter-gambles-one-supply-chain-strategy-offers-blueprint-45rqf&trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment_ellipsis-menu-semaphore-sign-in-redirect&guestReportContentType=COMMENT&_f=guest-reporting)\n\n[Mustafa](https://tr.linkedin.com/in/mustafatarcan?trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment-text), excellent insights! The Supply 2.0 challenge particularly resonates. Most companies excel at internal optimisation but struggle with that crucial leap to true supplier-to-distribution integration.\n\nThe breakthrough happens when leaders pinpoint why their end-to-end visibility breaks down, is it data silos between suppliers and logistics? Disconnected demand signals from distribution partners? Fragmented inventory visibility across the network?\n\nThe real accelerator is empowering cross-functional teams with unified data access. When procurement can see downstream impacts, when logistics can anticipate upstream delays, that's when Supply 2.0 integration actually works. Everyone's looking at the same reality, which drives stakeholder confidence and trust.\n\nI've seen this firsthand, companies that master supplier-to-distribution visibility before chasing Supply 3.0 consumer connectivity build much stronger foundations.\n\nWhat aspects of Supply 2.0 integration do you see companies struggle with most?\n\n[Like](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/cold-join?session_redirect=%2Fpulse%2Fhow-procter-gambles-one-supply-chain-strategy-offers-blueprint-45rqf&trk=article-ssr-frontend-pulse_x-social-details_comments-action_comment_like) [Reply](https://www.linkedin.com/signup/c